            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan with the <strong>red wine stock </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 7-8 min or until thickened and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>pork, fennel & red wine ragu</strong></p>",
